gm managed-gitignore mechanics (drained from AGENTS.md Core Rules iter-outside-box): .gm/rs-learn.db and .gm/code-search/ MUST stay tracked (shared memory/index across machines+CI). Because gitignore cannot re-include a path under an ignored parent dir (the parent-re-include caveat), the managed block NEVER ignores .gm/ wholesale; instead individual transient entries are listed one-by-one between the # >>> gm managed markers: prd-state.json, lastskill, turn-state.json, trajectory-drafts/, ingest-drafts/, rslearn-counter.json (plus runtime junk like .gm/witness/ and exec-spool staleness markers between # >>> plugkit managed markers). Writer: gm-plugkit/plugkit-wasm-wrapper.js::ensureGitignored(cwd, entry). That writer and every agent editing .gitignore must never add .gm/, .gm/rs-learn.db, .gm/code-search/, legacy .code-search/, or .gm/disciplines (any subpath) to ignore rules. All project-local persistent state (chunk index, DB, embeddings) writes under .gm/<name>/, never a top-level dotdir.